@wujun8 IMO, if your Filter with Annotation Activate, it will be activated by default. You do not need to config like `<dubbo:service filter="f1,f2"/>`.

@Activate doesn't means that it's internal, also may be user's custom filter, right?
/// Yes, u r right. But once your filter with this annotation, it will be performed.

u can refer this doc: http://dubbo.apache.org/zh-cn/docs/dev/impls/filter.html

If you want to activate a filter on a specify service, don't use the annotation.

@diecui1202 
I think a same pr should be sent to branch 2.6.x.
How do u think about it?

public class Test<E> extends ArrayList<E> {

    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

    private long total;
}

这样的类，jdk本身是可以序列化反序列化的。
但是dubbo接口不行。

什么原因？

My suggestion is:
Using Composite Style instead of Extend extension.
In your case, a more graceful design is:
```
@Data
public class Page{
private boolean count;
private int pageNum;
private int pageSize;
private int startRow;
...
private List<XXX> data;
}
```

@ZhuoSiChen 
public class Test<E> extends ArrayList<E> {

    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

    private long total;

    private int pages;

    private int pageNum;

    private int pageSize;

    public Test() {
    }

}

这样吗？结果还是一样。

@65725738 
原因找到了。
在Hessian序列时候它会先判断先判断这个类是不是基本的Collection.class而不是给你的类去新建一个 Serializer对象。详细debug SerializerFactory.getSerializer()方法。
